  "time_ut": 1659417119,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0db0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d85\u0dc4\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd6 \u0db4\u0db8\u0dab\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0db0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d85\u0dc4\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0db1\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Just because the ministership is abolished, the secretaryship is not abolished",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Justice Wijayadasa Rajapaksa said that the section of the Constitution which states that when a ministry is abolished, the position of the secretary of that ministry is also abolished through the 22nd Constitutional Amendment.",
        "Thus, just because a ministry is abolished, the secretary's position will not be abolished."
      ],
